37.41	Guillermo_Arriaga	Guillermo Arriaga	Guillermo Arriaga Jordán (Spanish pronunciation: ; born 13 March 1958) is a Mexican author, screenwriter, director and producer. Self-defined as “a hunter who works as a writer,” he authored Amores Perros, received a BAFTA Best Screenplay nomination for 21 Grams, and received the 2005 Cannes Best Screenplay Award for The Three Burials of Melquiades Estrada.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/GuillermoArriaga.jpg/200px-GuillermoArriaga.jpg
